Definition.WordDefinition: Fro \Fro\ (fr[=o]), adv. [OE. fra, fro, adv. & prep., Icel. fr[=a], akin to Dan. fra from, E. from. See {From}.] From; away; back or backward; -- now used only in opposition to the word to, in the phrase to and fro, that is, to and from. See {To and fro} under {To}. --Milton. [1913 Webster]
